The paper discusses the impact of inaccurate job size information on response time and fairness in size-based schedulers. This topic is relevant to operating systems (cs.OS) and distributed computing (cs.DC), as well as performance evaluation (cs.PF) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also presents a simulation-based evaluation, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG).
